mockit.integration.springframework

Class FakeBeanFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • mockit.MockUp<org.springframework.beans.factory.support.AbstractBeanFactory>
      • mockit.integration.springframework.FakeBeanFactory

  • public final class FakeBeanFactory
extends MockUp<org.springframework.beans.factory.support.AbstractBeanFactory>
    If applied, this fake will take over calls to AbstractBeanFactory.getBean(String) in any implementation class, returning instead a @Tested or @Injectable object with the given field name, or a dependency object injected at any level into a @Tested object.

    In case said calls come (indirectly) from a test class having no @Tested fields, bean lookup will proceed into the actual getBean(String) implementation method.

    Note this fake is only useful if the code under test makes direct calls to Spring's getBean(name) method.
